[
    {
        "number": "1",
        "stopTime": "00:00:03,120",
        "startTime": "00:00:00,080",
        "text": "Every YouTube video has a unique ID.\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "2",
        "stopTime": "00:00:05,770",
        "startTime": "00:00:03,120",
        "text": "It's up in the URL: a string of eleven characters\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "3",
        "stopTime": "00:00:08,820",
        "startTime": "00:00:05,770",
        "text": "that uniquely identifies which video you want.\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "4",
        "stopTime": "00:00:12,580",
        "startTime": "00:00:08,820",
        "text": "Now, YouTube has millions and millions of\nvideos.\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "5",
        "stopTime": "00:00:16,460",
        "startTime": "00:00:12,580",
        "text": "The last stats that they released said they\nhave\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "6",
        "stopTime": "00:00:20,380",
        "startTime": "00:00:16,460",
        "text": "400 hours of video being uploaded every minute.\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "7",
        "stopTime": "00:00:23,369",
        "startTime": "00:00:20,380",
        "text": "So: are they ever going to run out of those\nIDs?\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "8",
        "stopTime": "00:00:27,240",
        "startTime": "00:00:23,369",
        "text": "Well, to find out, let's talk about counting\nsystems.\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "9",
        "stopTime": "00:00:29,509",
        "startTime": "00:00:27,240",
        "text": "People count in Base 10. 0 to 9.\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "10",
        "stopTime": "00:00:31,949",
        "startTime": "00:00:29,509",
        "text": "That'll be, hopefully, familiar to you.\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "11",
        "stopTime": "00:00:34,060",
        "startTime": "00:00:31,949",
        "text": "Computers count in base 2, in binary,\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "12",
        "stopTime": "00:00:36,200",
        "startTime": "00:00:34,060",
        "text": "but that's difficult for humans to read,\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "13",
        "stopTime": "00:00:38,900",
        "startTime": "00:00:36,200",
        "text": "it gets too long to write really, really quickly,\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "14",
        "stopTime": "00:00:43,650",
        "startTime": "00:00:38,900",
        "text": "so often computers will display it in base\n16, hexadecimal.\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "15",
        "stopTime": "00:00:46,340",
        "startTime": "00:00:43,650",
        "text": "You have 0 to 9, and then A to F,\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "16",
        "stopTime": "00:00:49,040",
        "startTime": "00:00:46,340",
        "text": "and then you start adding to the next column.\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "17",
        "stopTime": "00:00:50,660",
        "startTime": "00:00:49,040",
        "text": "Humans can't understand that easily,\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "18",
        "stopTime": "00:00:53,400",
        "startTime": "00:00:50,660",
        "text": "but it's efficient if we have to type it in\nsomewhere,\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "19",
        "stopTime": "00:00:59,100",
        "startTime": "00:00:53,400",
        "text": "and 16 - 2 to the power of 4 - is also easy\nfor computers to deal with.\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "20",
        "stopTime": "00:01:00,790",
        "startTime": "00:00:59,100",
        "text": "So how about Base 64?\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "21",
        "stopTime": "00:01:05,360",
        "startTime": "00:01:00,790",
        "text": "That'd be a ridiculous counting system, right?\nExcept.\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "22",
        "stopTime": "00:01:08,000",
        "startTime": "00:01:05,360",
        "text": "64 is another one of those easy numbers for\ncomputers,\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "23",
        "stopTime": "00:01:10,370",
        "startTime": "00:01:08,000",
        "text": "it is 2 to the power of 6.\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "24",
        "stopTime": "00:01:12,750",
        "startTime": "00:01:10,370",
        "text": "And humans can get to 64 very easily:\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "25",
        "stopTime": "00:01:15,670",
        "startTime": "00:01:12,750",
        "text": "0 to 9, then capital letters A to Z,\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "26",
        "stopTime": "00:01:18,770",
        "startTime": "00:01:15,670",
        "text": "then small letters a to z, and two other characters.\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "27",
        "stopTime": "00:01:20,850",
        "startTime": "00:01:18,770",
        "text": "Most Base 64 uses slash and plus,\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "28",
        "stopTime": "00:01:22,810",
        "startTime": "00:01:20,850",
        "text": "but they don't work so well in URLs,\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "29",
        "stopTime": "00:01:25,830",
        "startTime": "00:01:22,810",
        "text": "so YouTube uses hyphen and underscore.\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "30",
        "stopTime": "00:01:28,090",
        "startTime": "00:01:25,830",
        "text": "That YouTube URL, that unique ID,\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "31",
        "stopTime": "00:01:32,270",
        "startTime": "00:01:28,090",
        "text": "is really just a random number in base 64.\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "32",
        "stopTime": "00:01:34,370",
        "startTime": "00:01:32,270",
        "text": "They could have have picked base 10 or base\n16,\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "33",
        "stopTime": "00:01:36,200",
        "startTime": "00:01:34,370",
        "text": "but they didn't: they went with 64,\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "34",
        "stopTime": "00:01:40,520",
        "startTime": "00:01:36,200",
        "text": "because it will let you cram a huge number\ninto a small space\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "35",
        "stopTime": "00:01:43,090",
        "startTime": "00:01:40,520",
        "text": "and still make it vaguely human readable.\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "36",
        "stopTime": "00:01:45,840",
        "startTime": "00:01:43,090",
        "text": "Author and programmer Sam Hughes, by the way,\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "37",
        "stopTime": "00:01:51,210",
        "startTime": "00:01:45,840",
        "text": "pushed this to the limit, and invented Base\n65,536,\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "38",
        "stopTime": "00:01:54,740",
        "startTime": "00:01:51,210",
        "text": "which includes basically every character from\nevery language.\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "39",
        "stopTime": "00:01:56,960",
        "startTime": "00:01:54,740",
        "text": "It is ridiculous and unnecessary,\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "40",
        "stopTime": "00:01:59,570",
        "startTime": "00:01:56,960",
        "text": "but when has that ever stopped programmers?\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "41",
        "stopTime": "00:02:04,659",
        "startTime": "00:01:59,570",
        "text": "So why didn't YouTube just start counting\nat 1 and work up?\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "42",
        "stopTime": "00:02:07,780",
        "startTime": "00:02:04,659",
        "text": "Well, first, they would have to synchronise\ntheir counting\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "43",
        "stopTime": "00:02:11,370",
        "startTime": "00:02:07,780",
        "text": "between all the servers handling the video\nuploads,\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "44",
        "stopTime": "00:02:14,400",
        "startTime": "00:02:11,370",
        "text": "or they'd have to assign each server a block\nof numbers.\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "45",
        "stopTime": "00:02:16,680",
        "startTime": "00:02:14,400",
        "text": "Either way, there's a lot of tracking to do,\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "46",
        "stopTime": "00:02:18,740",
        "startTime": "00:02:16,680",
        "text": "a lot of making sure that it's never duplicated.\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "47",
        "stopTime": "00:02:21,690",
        "startTime": "00:02:18,740",
        "text": "Instead, they just generate a random number\nfor each video,\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "48",
        "stopTime": "00:02:24,590",
        "startTime": "00:02:21,690",
        "text": "see if it's already taken, and if not, use\nit.\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "49",
        "stopTime": "00:02:28,090",
        "startTime": "00:02:24,590",
        "text": "And secondly, it is a really, really bad idea\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "50",
        "stopTime": "00:02:32,390",
        "startTime": "00:02:28,090",
        "text": "to just count 1, 2, 3 and so on in URLs.\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "51",
        "stopTime": "00:02:35,550",
        "startTime": "00:02:32,390",
        "text": "Incremental counters, as they're called, can\nbe a big security flaw:\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "52",
        "stopTime": "00:02:39,510",
        "startTime": "00:02:35,550",
        "text": "if you see video 283 up there, then you might\nwonder:\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "53",
        "stopTime": "00:02:42,260",
        "startTime": "00:02:39,510",
        "text": "what's video 284? Or video 282?\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "54",
        "stopTime": "00:02:43,990",
        "startTime": "00:02:42,260",
        "text": "It's easy to enumerate, as it's called,\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "55",
        "stopTime": "00:02:46,520",
        "startTime": "00:02:43,990",
        "text": "to run through the entire list.\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "56",
        "stopTime": "00:02:49,420",
        "startTime": "00:02:46,520",
        "text": "YouTube Unlisted videos, the ones that don't\nappear publicly\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "57",
        "stopTime": "00:02:52,450",
        "startTime": "00:02:49,420",
        "text": "but that you can send the link to people,\nthose wouldn't work.\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "58",
        "stopTime": "00:02:57,970",
        "startTime": "00:02:52,450",
        "text": "And by the way? Lots of badly designed sites\ndo use incremental counters.\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "59",
        "stopTime": "00:03:00,550",
        "startTime": "00:02:57,970",
        "text": "And it is a terrible idea.\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "60",
        "stopTime": "00:03:03,569",
        "startTime": "00:03:00,550",
        "text": "It might tell your competitors exactly how\nmany customers you have,\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "61",
        "stopTime": "00:03:04,880",
        "startTime": "00:03:03,569",
        "text": "'cos they can just count them.\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "62",
        "stopTime": "00:03:07,750",
        "startTime": "00:03:04,880",
        "text": "It might let people download all your records\neasily,\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "63",
        "stopTime": "00:03:08,810",
        "startTime": "00:03:07,750",
        "text": "'cos they can just run through them.\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "64",
        "stopTime": "00:03:12,920",
        "startTime": "00:03:08,810",
        "text": "And in one site that someone in Florida emailed\nme about this week,\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "65",
        "stopTime": "00:03:16,520",
        "startTime": "00:03:12,920",
        "text": "it lets you look at other people's personal\ndetails.\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "66",
        "stopTime": "00:03:21,380",
        "startTime": "00:03:16,520",
        "text": "Don't use incremental counters if you're building\na web site. Use a random number.\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "67",
        "stopTime": "00:03:22,930",
        "startTime": "00:03:21,380",
        "text": "Which brings me to the question:\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "68",
        "stopTime": "00:03:26,260",
        "startTime": "00:03:22,930",
        "text": "just how big are the numbers that YouTube\nuses?\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "69",
        "stopTime": "00:03:28,310",
        "startTime": "00:03:26,260",
        "text": "Well, let's work it out.\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "70",
        "stopTime": "00:03:32,310",
        "startTime": "00:03:28,310",
        "text": "One character of base 64 lets you have 64\nID numbers.\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "71",
        "stopTime": "00:03:37,569",
        "startTime": "00:03:32,310",
        "text": "Two characters? That's 64 by 64, or 4,096.\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "72",
        "stopTime": "00:03:42,610",
        "startTime": "00:03:37,569",
        "text": "Three characters? 64 times 64 times 64 -- or\n64 to the power of 3.\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "73",
        "stopTime": "00:03:45,560",
        "startTime": "00:03:42,610",
        "text": "That is already more than a quarter of a million.\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "74",
        "stopTime": "00:03:50,590",
        "startTime": "00:03:45,560",
        "text": "And if we go to four? Well, now we're above\n16 million.\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "75",
        "stopTime": "00:03:53,980",
        "startTime": "00:03:50,590",
        "text": "If you use Base 64, then you can assign an\nID number\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "76",
        "stopTime": "00:03:57,410",
        "startTime": "00:03:53,980",
        "text": "to everyone who lives in London down there\ntwice over,\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "77",
        "stopTime": "00:04:00,489",
        "startTime": "00:03:57,410",
        "text": "and you'll only need four characters.\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "78",
        "stopTime": "00:04:02,950",
        "startTime": "00:04:00,489",
        "text": "This gets big fast. We can keep on doing this,\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "79",
        "stopTime": "00:04:06,660",
        "startTime": "00:04:02,950",
        "text": "and by seven characters we're already at four\nquadrillion.\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "80",
        "stopTime": "00:04:10,300",
        "startTime": "00:04:06,660",
        "text": "Now, I assume that YouTube checks through\na dictionary,\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "81",
        "stopTime": "00:04:13,660",
        "startTime": "00:04:10,300",
        "text": "and doesn't allow any actual words to appear\nup there --\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "82",
        "stopTime": "00:04:15,250",
        "startTime": "00:04:13,660",
        "text": "particularly anything rude.\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "83",
        "stopTime": "00:04:18,669",
        "startTime": "00:04:15,250",
        "text": "But that is going to be a tiny minority of\nthe URLs,\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "84",
        "stopTime": "00:04:22,069",
        "startTime": "00:04:18,669",
        "text": "so for our purposes, we can pretty much just\nignore that.\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "85",
        "stopTime": "00:04:27,169",
        "startTime": "00:04:22,069",
        "text": "At YouTube's 11 characters, we are at 73 quintillion\n786 quadrillion\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "86",
        "stopTime": "00:04:30,589",
        "startTime": "00:04:27,169",
        "text": "976 trillion 294 billion 838 million\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "87",
        "stopTime": "00:04:32,479",
        "startTime": "00:04:30,589",
        "text": "206 thousand and 464 videos.\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "88",
        "stopTime": "00:04:35,669",
        "startTime": "00:04:32,479",
        "text": "That's enough for every single human on planet\nEarth\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "89",
        "stopTime": "00:04:41,629",
        "startTime": "00:04:35,669",
        "text": "to upload a video every minute for around\n18,000 years.\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "90",
        "stopTime": "00:04:42,599",
        "startTime": "00:04:41,629",
        "text": "YouTube planned ahead.\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "91",
        "stopTime": "00:04:45,889",
        "startTime": "00:04:42,599",
        "text": "Can they run out of URLs? Technically, yes.\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "92",
        "stopTime": "00:04:49,969",
        "startTime": "00:04:45,889",
        "text": "Practically? No. And if they did?\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "93",
        "stopTime": "00:04:52,559",
        "startTime": "00:04:49,969",
        "text": "They could just add one more character.\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "94",
        "stopTime": "00:04:56,180",
        "startTime": "00:04:53,640",
        "text": "[Translating these subtitles? Add your name here!]\n"
    },
    {
        "number": "95",
        "stopTime": "00:05:02,960",
        "startTime": "00:04:57,320",
        "text": "Ha! One take! One take! Yes!\n"
    }
]